# arvo-transparent. Design

The transparent-wrapper substrate. Defines the trait every
`repr(transparent)` arvo type implements to expose its inner container
in const context, and the free function that consumes it. No fielded
types. `#![no_std]`, no alloc.

Depends on `notko` only.

## Transparent

```rust
pub const unsafe trait Transparent {
    type Inner;
    fn raw(self) -> Self::Inner;
}
```

`pub const unsafe trait`: the `unsafe` reflects the `repr(transparent)`
soundness obligation (the implementor must guarantee the layout is
identical to `Inner`). The `const` reflects that the default `raw()`
body uses `transmute_copy` and is callable in const context.

The default body:

```rust
default fn raw(self) -> Self::Inner {
    unsafe { core::mem::transmute_copy(&self) }
}
```

Implementors that want a different body can override; most accept the
default.

## NumericPrimitive

```rust
pub trait NumericPrimitive {}
```

Clean marker. Identifies the bottom-out primitives that arvo wrappers
ultimately transmute to: `u8`, `u16`, `u32`, `u64`, `usize`, `bool`,
`i8`, `i16`, `i32`, `i64`, `isize`. No methods. Used as a bound where
arvo trait machinery needs to know "this is the primitive layer, stop
recursing".

Per round 202604271346 D-11, this returns to its clean marker-only
role. No `from_u64_masked`, `to_u64`, or per-size method on this
trait.

## Free arvo::raw fn

```rust
pub const fn raw<W, T>(w: W) -> T
where
    W: [const] Transparent<Inner = T>,
{
    w.raw()
}
```

Re-exported from the `arvo` facade as `arvo::raw`. Prefix-style
ergonomic for `transmute_copy`-via-trait. Callable in const fn bodies.

